The Assistant Inspector General of Police in Charge of Zone 2, AIG, Ahmed Iliyasu, on Tuesday paraded four suspected killers of a businessman who owns Fireman Generator, Ignatius Adunukwe and buried him in swampy area in Ogombo, Ajah area of Lagos. Iliyasu who paraded the four suspected murder explained that a new and highly sophisticated dimension has been introduced into cybercrime. He said,’’ Firstly, it was Yahoo-yahoo we have be contending with but now we battle Yahoo plus until the discovery this one which is about the deadliest in the annals of internet frauds. “No one is free from them as long as you are on the social media. “The only way out is to abstain from unnecessary and flagrant flaunting of one’s achievement and wealth on social media.” He said members of this syndicate are so callous that they hack into your Facebook account, peruse your profile and once they find anything appealing to them in you “as a big fish” all they do is to start working on you. “They would start sending you a friend request and the moment you respond in the affirmative you already a target. “They would start by selling dummies of business ideas in your area of specialty to you and human nature.” AIG added that, ” To be paraded today are four suspects who orchestrated the killing of the gang’s latest victim which their despicable conduct connotes a high level of wickedness, hinged on abysmal loss of moral values. “One Ignatius Adunukwe, a successful businessman and Philanthropist who was into Estate Development and Gold Mining fell victim of this heartless syndicate and now his virtually murdered,” he said. According to him, ‘’He left his place residence N0.14, Makinde Street, off Raymond Njoku Street, South- West Ikoyi in Lagos on December 1, 2019 and never to return home.’’ However, the suspects were identified as Daniel BOB Ibeaji, 42; Arinze Uzor Igwe, 26; Solomon Cletus, 30 and Israel Obigaremu,35. 